@reebok and @baitme come together to release the latest iteration of the Instapump Fury model, clad in the colors of several @toystory characters. The sneakers come in mismatching colors for each foot. The left side is dressed in palettes of purple and green, referencing tones of Buzz Lightyear. The right foot Complete with black and white cow-patterns at the side panel, light blue denim underlays are placed next to hits of yellow, a reference to Sheriff Woody. The sneaker will see a limited release in celebration for the screening of the upcoming Toy Story 4.Photos: BAIT

@openingceremony and @vans have unveiled their latest footwear collaboration, this time around dressing the Old Skool sneaker in a lux satin shell. The shoe will be available in three vibrant colorways in line with the summer season, and will be available for purchase on June 21st for $100 at Opening Ceremony‘s retail and online stores.Photo: @bye.loveleo

PostsDetails.description: @crocs has teamed up with @barneysny for two punk-inspired makeovers. Both pairs feature pins that reiterate Barney’s creative touches - the first pair features a safety pin dangles individual letters to spell out “Barneys,” and a block typeface pin reads “NYC.” The second pair features a blue denim that’s matched with smooth black leather on the toe potion. They are currently available for purchase at Barneys New York online store for $90 USD.Photo: Barneys

@converse returns with a new iteration of the Chuck 70. The silhouette's canvas upper is dressed in a flame-shaped gradient scheme of purple, turquoise, yellow and orange above a stark black base. Cop a pair at select retailers like @brownsfashion for $75 USD.Photo: Browns

@affixworks teams up with @asics for two limited edition iterations of the GEL KINSEI runner. The runner combines functional workwear elements with streetwear design cues, such as bold color combinations to create a colorful aesthetic. Tune in to the AFFIX SOUND SYSTEM livestream on June 21 from 5PM CEST for a chance to cop a pair.Photo: AFFIX

@virgilabloh and @futuradosmil have given a first look at an upcoming @nike Dunk Low collaboration, coming in either bold orange with dark blue detailing or “UNC” light blue. Both colorways feature Abloh and Futura’s signatures on the underside, which is visible through the semi-translucent sole unit. Stay tuned for pricing and release information.Photo: Pete Casta/HYPEBEAST France

@vans celebrates Pride month with an exclusive release at the brand’s @vansvault store in New York. The two-piece capsule consists of the Sk8-Hi and the Classic Slip-On silhouettes. Both are covered with the word “love” in a range of different languages and colors, intended to celebrate inclusion and the city’s diverse global community. Cop a pair now at the Vault by Vans store.Photo: Vans

@adidas has just released the second generation POD-S3.2, a camouflaged take on the new silhouette. The sneaker’s yellow colorway features a BAPE-like camo shell that’s decked with sueded overlays and black laces for contrast, which sits on top of a midsole that is constructed of white brown and beige for a colorblocked design to house the signature BOOST system.
